Durban - South African Police Services Search and Rescue officers have retrieved the body of a second 10-year old from a canal on Monday morning. The discovery comes just a day after the body of a boy was found in the dense bushy area alongside the canal on Saturday afternoon. Last week, two boys from a Clairwood primary school were reported missing. The youngsters, Luyanda Msomi and Njabulo Mankayi, were last seen boarding a bus after school on Thursday. When the boys failed to return home, a missing personâ€™s report was filed at Brighton Beach police station. On Saturday, police were notified about the body of one of the boys. Upon arrival, it was discovered that the body belongs to Luyanda. An extensive search was set up for Njabulo, however by Sunday evening, officials were not able to locate him. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
